&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are seeking an experienced and detail-oriented&amp;nbsp;Controller to lead all aspects of financial reporting,&amp;nbsp;accounting operations, and consolidation for our U.S.&lt;br&gt;subsidiary based in King of Prussia, Pennsylvania.&lt;br&gt;Reporting directly to the Group Controller, the Controller&amp;nbsp;will serve as the primary liaison between the local&amp;nbsp;finance function and the parent company&#39;s global&amp;nbsp;finance team, Ensuring full alignment with group,&amp;nbsp;reporting standards, US GAAP, IFRS and internal control&lt;br&gt;frameworks.&lt;br&gt;This is a high-impact, highly visible role suited for a&amp;nbsp;finance leader who thrives in a dynamic, multi-entity&lt;br&gt;environment and can balance operational rigor with&amp;nbsp;strategic insight.&lt;br&gt;The Controller is the financial backbone of our U.S.&amp;nbsp;operations — translating business activity into reliable,&amp;nbsp;timely, and insightful reporting that drives confident&amp;nbsp;decision-making across the organization.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Reporting &amp;amp; Consolidation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Own the preparation and delivery of accurate monthly, quarterly, and&amp;nbsp;annual financial statements in accordance with IFRS and parent company&amp;nbsp;reporting requirements&lt;br&gt;2. Lead the consolidation process for the U.S. subsidiary, including&amp;nbsp;intercompany eliminations and reconciliations with the global parent&amp;nbsp;entity&lt;br&gt;3. Manage the month-end and year-end close process, ensuring&amp;nbsp;completeness, accuracy, and adherence to strict deadlines&lt;br&gt;4. Coordinate with external auditors and oversee the annual audit process&amp;nbsp;from planning through completion&lt;br&gt;5. Prepare management reports, variance analysis, and financial&amp;nbsp;commentary for senior leadership and the parent company&#39;s finance team&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accounting Operations &amp;amp; Internal Controls&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Oversee day-to-day accounting functions including general ledger, accounts payable, accounts receivable, fixed assets, and payroll&amp;nbsp;accounting&lt;br&gt;2. Design, implement, and monitor internal controls to safeguard company assets and ensure financial integrity&lt;br&gt;3. Maintain and enhance accounting policies and procedures in compliance with both local and group standards&lt;br&gt;4. Manage the company&#39;s tax compliance obligations, including federal,&amp;nbsp;state, and local filings, in coordination with external tax advisors&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Partnership &amp;amp; Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Partner with FP&amp;amp;A and business unit leaders to provide financial insights&amp;nbsp;that support budgeting, forecasting, and strategic planning&lt;br&gt;2. Lead and mentor a team of accounting professionals, fostering a high performance and continuous-improvement culture&lt;br&gt;3. Drive ERP and system optimization initiatives to improve reporting&amp;nbsp;efficiency and data accuracy&lt;br&gt;4. Support M&amp;amp;A due diligence, integration activities, and ad hoc financial&amp;nbsp;projects as required&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Electrical engineering team leader, you will be a contributing member and leader of a new product development team, responsible for the design, simulation, analysis, testing, and integration of hardware.&lt;br&gt;You will provide technical leadership to a project team to achieve product performance, production, quality, cost, and schedule objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for all team deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for team members mentoring “Hands-on”&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sc. in Electrical engineering. - Must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 5 years of Experience in Analog and/or Power electronics designs (AC/DC, DC/DC topologies design, Analog circuits design, Operational Amplifiers circuits, Familiarity with modern power components, Noise and Signal integrity concerns. -Must.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years of proven experience in a Board and PCBA design – Must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and familiarity with hardware design for FPGAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microcontrollers DSP and SOM (Xilinx, ST, Intel SOM modules advantage)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in VHDL/Verilog at least 3 years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with interfaces/protocols – PCIe, DDR 3 or 4. - Must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity&amp;nbsp;with the common inter chip communication protocols:(I2C, SPI, UART/USART, QSPI). - Must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Electrical engineering team leader, you will be a contributing member and leader of a new product development team, responsible for the design, simulation, analysis, testing, and integration of hardware.&lt;br&gt;You will provide technical leadership to a project team to achieve product performance, production, quality, cost, and schedule objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for all team deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for team members mentoring “Hands-on”&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sc. in Electrical engineering. - Must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2 years of Experience in Analog and/or Power electronics designs (AC/DC, DC/DC topologies design, Analog circuits design, Operational Amplifiers circuits, Familiarity with modern power components, Noise and Signal integrity concerns. -Must.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 3 years of proven experience in a Board and PCBA design – Must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and familiarity with hardware design for FPGAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microcontrollers DSP and SOM (Xilinx, ST, Intel SOM modules advantage)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in VHDL/Verilog at least 3 years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with interfaces/protocols – PCIe, DDR 3 or 4. - Must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity&amp;nbsp;with the common inter chip communication protocols:(I2C, SPI, UART/USART, QSPI). - Must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who Are We?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Electreon is a trailblazer in the EV industry, leading the way with our innovative wireless charging technology. Recognized globally with multiple awards, we’re transforming transportation by making vehicle charging smarter, more efficient, and more accessible. With a deep commitment to sustainability and innovation, we envision a world where wireless charging powers the future of mobility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At &lt;strong&gt;Electreon&lt;/strong&gt;, we’re not just creating technology – we’re building the future of electric mobility. And to make that happen, we need talented, forward-thinking individuals like you! 💡✨&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Didn’t see a role that fits? No worries! We’re always interested in connecting with passionate, creative minds who want to make an impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;📩 &lt;strong&gt;Send us your CV&lt;/strong&gt;, showcase your skills, and let’s stay in touch. The right opportunity may be just around the corner!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come and charge up Your Career With Us!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Who We Are?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Electreon is a pioneer of wireless charging for the EV industry. Our groundbreaking award-winning technology is reshaping the future of transportation, making vehicle charging more efficient and accessible. With a passion for sustainability and innovation, we&#39;re dedicated to a future where wireless charging powers our roads and vehicles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us to reimagine the future of transportation!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading testing assignments in house, at subcontractors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;follow and improve systems testing procedures and testbenches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing a solution for a wide range of projects in Israel and abroad under time constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform integration and perform full performance analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement testing systems &amp;amp; ATP according to R&amp;amp;D specifications for all of the products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability to site deployment and customer support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a similar position - required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronics practical engineer with two years experience - required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of system testing and card integration to sub-assembly - required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of reading drawings and electrical diagrams - required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level English - required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with high voltage - Advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electricity license - Advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to fly abroad (few times a quarter).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;* Reference is intended for both women and men&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;** Only appropriate inquiries will be answered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Mechanical Design Engineer Leader&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are we&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Electreon is a publicly traded Israeli company, developing and implementing Wireless Electric Road Systems (ERS) a shared, invisible platform that wirelessly charges commercial and passenger electric vehicles while driving. By significantly decreasing battery size, cost and weight and improving operational efficiency, Electreon offers governments, cities and fleet operators the most sustainable and cost-effective solution towards 100% global electrification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a part of the R&amp;amp;D mechanical team you&#39;ll lead and design the required solutions for a high-end Wireless charging system. From the stages of concept definition to successful implementation. You&#39;ll have full ownership of the mechanical design, including analysis, testing, manufacturing, validation and integration. you&#39;ll collaborate with cross-functional design teams such as hardware, electronics, and software. &lt;br&gt;And you will be an integral part of a dynamic environment with great team energy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role involves providing support for production and ensuring compliance with deadlines, quality and cost targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sc. / M.Sc. in Mechanical Engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An experienced Mechanical Design engineer with 8 years of experience in product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3D CAD &amp;amp; PLM experience (SolidWorks/PDM preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in complex Electro Mechanical designs. knowledge in Heat dissipation solutions and thermal management systems, PCB design, electrical packaging and design for large scale manufacturing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;knowledge in High flux heat dissipation, structural analysis, materials, coatings, High voltage isolation, sealing, DFM &amp;amp; geometrical tolerances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advantage- knowledge of Different production techniques including CNC, compaction, Sheet Metal, welding and 3D printing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advantage- knowledge with Automotive &amp;amp; EV standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively communicate product architectures, design proposals and negotiate options at management levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player, problem-solving attitude and excellent interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience for projects and flexible mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is located at Bait Yanai, Israel&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;row row-site mt6 mb9&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;column large-10 large-centered&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;career-content&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;15&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;15&quot;&gt;Who We Are?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;17&quot; data-end=&quot;360&quot;&gt;Electreon is a pioneer in wireless charging for the EV industry. Our groundbreaking, award-winning technology is reshaping the future of transportation by making vehicle charging more efficient and accessible. With a passion for sustainability and innovation, we are committed to a future where wireless charging powers our roads and vehicles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;362&quot; data-end=&quot;417&quot;&gt;Join us to help reimagine the future of transportation!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;419&quot; data-end=&quot;440&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;419&quot; data-end=&quot;440&quot;&gt;What Will You Do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;442&quot; data-end=&quot;885&quot;&gt;We are seeking an experienced &lt;strong data-start=&quot;472&quot; data-end=&quot;491&quot;&gt;Program Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;with extensive R&amp;amp;D experience to lead our projects and manage relationships with our partners. As a Project Manager, you will guide the engineering team, including system engineering, and play a key role in defining technical strategies. You will be involved in major architectural and strategic decisions that shape the growth and evolution of our teams and technical interfaces with clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;887&quot; data-end=&quot;1426&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;887&quot; data-end=&quot;952&quot;&gt;Lead all aspects of the project, from kick-off to delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;953&quot; data-end=&quot;1022&quot;&gt;Oversee the development process and ensure business value delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1053&quot; data-end=&quot;1093&quot;&gt;Manage the R&amp;amp;D project Gantt chart and budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1094&quot; data-end=&quot;1175&quot;&gt;Assist in implementing visions of quality, agility, trust, and timely delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1176&quot; data-end=&quot;1307&quot;&gt;Collaborate with clients, HQ R&amp;amp;D, and supply chain teams, including subsidiaries in the US, Germany, Sweden, and other locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1308&quot; data-end=&quot;1426&quot;&gt;Lead technology implementation with strategic partners such as OEMs, Tier 1 suppliers, and infrastructure companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1308&quot; data-end=&quot;1426&quot;&gt;This position includes occasional international travel for short business trips.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1428&quot; data-end=&quot;1445&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1428&quot; data-end=&quot;1445&quot;&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 7 years of experience as a Development Project Manager in a multidisciplinary company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in either direct people management or matrix management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in managing diverse, high-budget development programs involving mechanical, electronic, and software components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience in leading complex system integration processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong expertise in requirements management and technical aspects of product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to plan, track, and deliver according to project schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High proficiency in English, both written and spoken.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the automotive industry - an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineering degree - an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in a start-up environment - an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Electreon is developing a unique cloud-based IoT system for charging vehicles wirelessly and on-the-go. As a Strategic buyer, you will independently perform the full range of purchasing duties in accordance with the established policies and procedures of Electreon. This will include material sourcing, supplier development, inventory control, and process improvements to decrease the total cost of ownership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with other internal departments and external vendors to ensure that the company’s finished products meet our customers’ expectations of superior quality and on time delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sourcing and locating suppliers and other supply sources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate with suppliers and reduce costs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Issue purchase orders while auditing required quantities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receipt of quotations, approval of invoices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improving relationships with suppliers – conditions, quality, delivery times, availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management and control of suppliers relations from the local/global market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivery, operation, logistical coordination, and order tracking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assimilation of procurement methodologies in the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subcontractors supply management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years’ experience in a similar position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the field of electronics purchasing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge and experience in the US market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with mechanical packaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-level English –verbal and written.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work experience in an ERP environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to work non-routine hours.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advantages&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of international standards – a significant advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in managing purchasing from a global company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge in technical procurement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NPI buyer – a significant advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;We are seeking an ideal candidate who embodies experience, proactivity, and a collaborative spirit. Someone who is genuinely excited about our company&#39;s technology and its sustainable, innovative approach to electric vehicle charging. We are in search of a creative system engineer who possesses a profound understanding of multidisciplinary systems, coupled with strong technical leadership skills and a background in electronic power design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defining product specifications and system requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guiding R&amp;amp;D teams, encompassing electrical, mechanical, and software engineers, throughout all design phases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overseeing design verification and validation processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Playing an integral role in system architectural design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serving as the technical authority and primary point of contact with the customer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading system standardization efforts for the EU and US markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor&#39;s degree in Electrical Engineering – Mandatory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 3 years of intensive experience as a system engineer on multidisciplinary products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evolving from a background in electronic development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with standardization processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge in high-power systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in designing high-power/high-current systems and onboard auxiliary power systems – Considered a significant advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience within the automotive industry – Beneficial.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional experience in VHDL, ARM, SOM, Embedded, and IoT – Also advantageous.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Warehouse Specialist you will be responsible for integral duties related to the transport and receipt of Electreon parts and products. Further duties include basic warehouse and inventory functions, proper handling of products, and the ability to maintain and manipulate documentation for record keeping. You will have the opportunity to work as part of a growing team in a fast-expanding field, and we will foster a positive environment to hone your skill set and cultivate your potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm and process shipments promptly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document all shipments from customers, vendors, and contract manufacturers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adept interdepartmental communication and follow-up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule and trace domestic and international shipments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manipulate packaging for product and prototype shipments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with inventory-related functions including cycle counts, audits, requisitions, and systems upkeep&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Quality Assurance to ensure policy and procedural compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aid in export and import compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive and verify all incoming packages and deliver to employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain adequate inventory of shipping materials and supplies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accept, inspect, and document freight deliveries, and coordinate movement with appropriate parties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safe use of pallet jacks, ladders, power drills, and other shop tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in meticulous data maintenance and manipulation in Microsoft Excel and database software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;S., Business, Logistics or similar area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-3 years of shipping and receiving experience, including export and import for both domestic and international shipments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of lookup functions and table manipulation in Microsoft Excel; Diligent data maintenance is paramount in this role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate the ability to self-start, swiftly solve problems, and ask questions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exhibit the capacity to work well with others while handling multiple issues simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain composure under pressure in a rapidly-evolving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to safely lift loads up to 50 pounds with rotation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to navigate our warehouse spaces and reach items both high and low&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent documentation and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with domestic and international shipping terminology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to demonstrate attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forklift Operator certification strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k) matching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Equity Shares&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dental Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vision Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Short-Term, Long-Term Disability and Life Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Time Off&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
